  "auditPrinciples": [
    "AuditRecord is owned by Governance & Security.",
    "AuditRecord is not automatically an EvidenceRecord.",
    "EvidenceReference may reference an AuditRecord when required.",
    "Every security decision must be auditable.",
    "Every business mutation and lifecycle transition must be auditable.",
    "Every control operation must be auditable.",
    "Sensitive reads and exports must be auditable.",
    "Package state and entitlement transitions must be auditable.",
    "Authentication success and failure must follow security audit policy.",
    "Service-identity operations must identify the machine actor.",
    "Audit failure must never silently convert a denied action into an allowed action.",
    "Secrets, credentials and full tokens must never enter AuditRecord.",
    "Audit identifiers and trace identifiers must be stable and non-secret.",
    "Audit storage implementation is outside this task.",
    "Local Reports JSONL is legacy compatibility only, not the target audit system of record."
  ],
